I won two Emmy’s this weekend lmao. Thank you @rachelshukert for texting me in April 2020 and being like “um hi do you want to write for season two of The Baby-Sitters Club?” It was the beginning of lockdown aka I was peak les miz and the opportunity to spend a few hours a day with fellow future Emmy winners @rheeqsquared @saschagrothchild @danjrobert and @lishasbrooks sounded like heaven on earth. And it was. Getting lost in Stoneybrook and into the minds of these 12 year-old girls was the perfect antidote to living in a world IRL that was literally and metaphorically burning down. Thank you @thombrowne for the look. Stacey McGill would’ve approved. (Photo by Marc Bryan Brown)

three years ago i quit drinking! as a culture we are so alcohol-pilled. i legit think i kept drinking for another two years because i couldn't imagine not getting wasted at my annual vacation to provincetown, which is insane??? anyway, @thisnakedmind got me sober. if you're in a TBD relationship with drinking, take a gander! the goal isn't always sobriety. it's thinking more critically about drinking. tbh, i do think alcohol is a scam largely perpetuated by capitalism to keep us spending money to drink literal poison but that's just me :)

i used to take all these photos of my drinks because i thought they looked glam? truly deranged. anyway, not drinking slaps. you get your life back, all of it belongs to you, even the parts that aren't chic, which weirdly still feels great, and you get hotter. the second i stopped drinking, my body went from being a human wine cellar to just being My Body. slay.....

2023 was weird and the fact that I barely took any pictures reflects that. Years where you have to grow and “realize stuff” are annoying but not as annoying as not growing or realizing stuff. Anyway, here’s a random chaotic collection of photos that capture a random chaotic year.
1. Getting STD tested. I got my first one ever this year! #bookedandblessed  2. I’m obsessed with flowers and my dining room table. My camera roll is essentially nudes and home decor.  3. @marcbendavid lent me his bf’s sweater and it really resonated with me.  4. CEO’s of Fuck These People dinner parties  5. I took this picture of my ass in the bathroom of my dentist’s office in Westwood. Like other years, I spent 2023 largely consumed with the state of my ass.  6. I ate a soft serve sundae in Toronto that really struck a chord.  7. Carnage from one of our parties. Was it @amateurgourmet and @csj214’s going away? Can’t remember. I love throwing parties and getting everyone I love under my roof.  8. @ecareyo and @simonjhaas got married in Laurel Canyon and it was perfect. Still get chills from them walking down the aisle to Mazzy Star.  9. @jprampage and I went to Europe and instead of taking pics of art and monuments I took pictures of things like this and I’m okay with that.
10. Got to dress like a whore at The Getty for literature purposes. I feel lucky that I get to do random shit like this. It’s moment like these where I’m like, “ Yes, I have built my life correctly. I am living the life that I’ve always wanted to lead.”
